rComments: The class is interesting, especially if you already are intrigued by the topic. Brewster is very smart, and I think he thinks his students to be just as smart, so his tests were very difficult and very unlike the homeworks, which were very straightforward. Overall, I did well in the class, but probably because everyone else did so poorly.
Great professor, homework is reasonably straight forward but an assignment is due every single class. Tests are very focused on derivations and can be brutal. Overall would recommend.
